{
  "doc_id": "14909",
  "text": "Two brainstem areas in particular, the pontine reticular formation (PRF) and the locus coeruleus (LC), are well studied as potential mediators of anesthetic action. The PRF is an important structure in promoting the cortical activation associated with wake and REM [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Neurotransmitters in the PRF such as adenosine, hypocretin/orexin, glutamate, GABA, and acetylcholine are each known to modulate arousal state [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] .",
